-- Orient Plans to Start Credit-Card Business in China by 2012, Sankei Says
-- Naoko Fujimura
-- 2010-06-28T22:44:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/orient-plans-to-start-credit-card-business-in-china-by-2012-sankei-says.html

          
          
             Orient Corp. plans to start a
credit-card business in China by 2012 to target buyers of cars
and electronics, the Sankei newspaper said, citing an interview
with President Yoshimasa Nishida. Orient would be the first
Japanese credit service company to enter China, the report said.  
